msgctxt "248"
msgid "You got the <Color:8>Briefcase with 30 Million Yen<Color:Default>."
msgstr "Obtuviste un <Color:8>maletín con 30 millones de yenes<Color:Default>."

msgctxt "2880"
msgid "Akiyama"
msgstr "Akiyama"

msgctxt "2884"
msgid "Hana"
msgstr "Hana"

msgctxt "2888"
msgid "Talk_Yes"
msgstr "Talk_Yes"

msgctxt "2892"
msgid "Talk_Call"
msgstr "Talk_Call"

msgctxt "2896"
msgid "dummy"
msgstr "dummy"

msgctxt "2900"
msgid "0"
msgstr "0"

msgctxt "212_Akiyama"
msgid "Hana-chan. Is the money all set?"
msgstr "Hana-chan, ¿tienes el dinero listo?"

msgctxt "224_Hana"
msgid "Yep. Thirty million yen. I put it in a briefcase for you."
msgstr "Como usted ordenó. Treinta millones de yenes. Todo está en un maletín."

msgctxt "236_Akiyama"
msgid "Thanks. Appreciate you always being on top of things. It\\r\n"\n"helps a lot."
msgstr "Te agradezco que siempre estés al tanto de todo.\\r\n"\n"Eres de gran ayuda."

msgctxt "272_Akiyama"
msgid "Apparently, the exchange point is the taxi stand near the\\r\n"\n"Kamurocho Hills construction site."
msgstr "Al parecer, el punto de encuentro es la parada de taxis cerca del\\r\n"\n"sitio de obras de Kamurocho Hills."

msgctxt "284_Hana"
msgid "Well, it's your money, Chief. I'm not going to tell you how\\r\n"\n"to use it..."
msgstr "Es su dinero, jefe. No tengo intención de decirle cómo\\r\n"\n"manejarlo..."

msgctxt "296_Akiyama"
msgid "I'm sorry. I always make you go along with my crazy plans."
msgstr "Perdona. Siempre te meto en mis locuras."

msgctxt "308_Hana"
msgid "Don't worry about it. I do this job because I want to."
msgstr "No se preocupe. Hago esto por mi propia voluntad."

msgctxt "320_Hana"
msgid "Just be careful, all right? You have a habit of getting\\r\n"\n"caught up in shady deals."
msgstr "Solo tenga cuidado, ¿sí? Tiene la costumbre de\\r\n"\n"involucrarse en tratos sospechosos."

msgctxt "332_Akiyama"
msgid "I know. I will. Now, if you'll excuse me, I've got a date\\r\n"\n"over at the lockers."
msgstr "Lo sé. Lo sé. Ahora, si me disculpas, tengo que ir\\r\n"\n"a los casilleros."

